						<summary>

						<p>Slab forming the west wall of the Vīrabhadra shrine on the south side of the Bhīmēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned on the basis of paleography to the 8th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It states that Koḍivillu, son of Duggarāju made a gift of land to Rachchayiṟṟi, which can be sown with 10 <hi rend="italic">tūmus</hi> of the grains <hi rend="italic">āṟlu.</hi> The grant was stated to have been made at the instance of a certain Podaru Cheṟayurāju. It further states that the gift was to be protected by the officials <hi rend="italic">raṭoḍi</hi> and <hi rend="italic">kāpulu</hi> of Inmaḷūru and also records the gift 10 <hi rend="italic">tūmus</hi> of land, as described above, to the engraver <hi rend="italic">(vaḍagi).</hi> The engraver was Uḷimeṟe Prabhurāmunṟu.</p>						

						</summary>
